## OpenAI - Vector embeddings

OpenAIâ€™s text embeddings measure the relatedness of text strings.

Source: [Guideline](https://platform.openai.com/docs/guides/embeddings) |
[API Reference](https://platform.openai.com/docs/api-reference/embeddings)

```python
from typing import List
from openai import OpenAI

client = OpenAI(max_retries=5)

# (assuming ~800 tokens per page)
embedding_model_small = "text-embedding-3-small"    # 62,500 pages per dollar, Performance on MTEB eval: 62.3%
embedding_model_large = "text-embedding-3-large"    #  9,615 pages per dollar, Performance on MTEB eval: 64.6%
embedding_model_ada_002 = "text-embedding-ada-002"  # 12,500 pages per dollar, Performance on MTEB eval: 61.0%


def get_embedding(text: str, model=embedding_model_small, **kwargs) -> List[float]:
    # replace newlines, which can negatively affect performance.
    text = text.replace("\n", " ")

    response = client.embeddings.create(input=[text], model=model, **kwargs)

    return response.data[0].embedding
```

```python
import numpy as np

def normalize_l2(x):
    x = np.array(x)
    if x.ndim == 1:
        norm = np.linalg.norm(x)
        if norm == 0:
            return x
        return x / norm
    else:
        norm = np.linalg.norm(x, 2, axis=1, keepdims=True)
        return np.where(norm == 0, x, x / norm)


all_embedding = get_embedding("Your text string goes here", model=embedding_model_small);

cut_dim = all_embedding[:256]
normalize_reduced_embedding = normalize_l2(cut_dim)

print(cut_dim)
print(normalize_reduced_embedding)
```
